"indappledgrovesguide-inworldcrafting-title": "Game Mechanic: In-World Crafting",
"indappledgrovesguide-inworldcrafting-text": 
"<font weight='bold' align='center'>In-World Crafting</font>
	In-World Crafting works to remove the dependence on the crafting 
grid to create a more immersive experience. In Dappled Groves applies
this principle by providing two new mechanics to your woodworking
adventures.

	The first mechanic is the ability to process wood without the grid.
You can place a log, log slab, or piece of firewood on the ground and
interact with it with a tool such as an <a href=\"handbook://item-axe-chert\">axe</a>, <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:adze-wood-flint\">adze</a>, or <a href=\"handbook://item-saw-copper\">saw</a>. The results depend on the tool used and the selected <a href=\"handbook://toolmodes-indappledgroves\">toolmode</a>.  For instance, a <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:grubaxe-tinbronze\">Grub Axe</a> set to hewing used on a log will produce bark, while selecting the chopping tool mode will result in log slabs.

	<a href=\"handbook://workstations-indappledgroves\">Workstations</a> are the second mechanic. These currently include the
chopping block and saw buck. These workstations serve to provide a boost to efficiency when processing recipes
on them. Like before, the <a href=\"handbook://toolmodes-indappledgroves\">toolmode</a> of your tool alters the results.

	Working materials on or off of a <a href=\"handbook://workstations-indappledgroves\">workstation</a> is done the same way. 
Simply target the block and hold down the right-mouse button. The
working animation will begin, and soon you'll see your results. Wood
types vary in their hardness, so the time required may vary. Pine is a 
softer wood, and will process quickly. Ebony is one of the world's
hardest woods, and will take significantly longer, especially with
stone tools.",

	//Workstation Guide
"indappledgrovesguide-workstations-title": "Game Mechanic: Workstation Crafting",
"indappledgrovesguide-workstations-text": "<font weight='bold' align='center'>Workstation Crafting</font>
In Dappled Groves introduces new workstations to aid you in your woodworking endeavours. These workstations reduce the time required to complete woodworking operations such as chopping <a href=\"handbook://block-log-placed-birch-ud\">logs</a> into <a href=\"handbook://block-indappledgroves:logslab-birch-barked-down-free\">log slabs.</a>
<font weight='bold' align='center'>Workstations</font>
<font weight='bold' align='left'>Chopping Block</font><a href=\"handbook://block-indappledgroves:choppingblock-birch-east\">chopping block</a>
   The first workstation most will craft is the <a href=\"handbook://block-indappledgroves:choppingblock-birch-east\">chopping block</a>.  Like all workstations, it speeds up the processes performed on it, and may provide access to recipes not available via in-world crafting in the future.
	 Currently it is used for <a href=\"handbook://toolmodes-indappledgroves\">chopping</a> and <a href=\"handbook://toolmodes-indappledgroves\">hewing</a> processes, but cannot be used to make additional chopping blocks.

<font weight='bold' align='left'>SawBuck</font>
	The sawbuck becomes available after you craft <a href=\"handbook://item-boards\">boards</a>. As with the chopping block, it speeds up processes performed on it, and is used for <a href=\"handbook://toolmodes-indappledgroves\">sawing</a> logs into boards.

<font weight='bold' align='left'>Saw Horse</font>
   This workstation isn't introduced in the current release. However, it will be integrated later providing a variety of woodworking options involving the use of planers and other tools.",


//Tool Modes Guide
"indappledgrovesguide-toolmodes-title": "Game Mechanic: Tool Modes",
"indappledgrovesguide-toolmodes-text": 
"<font weight='bold' align='center'>Tool Modes</font>
	Tool modes provide options in how a tool is used, and can be changed
by pressing the F key while holding a tool that has them. In vanilla, 
tool modes can be seen with the chisel and prospecting pick. This mod
adds these options to other tools to provide more dynamic crafting
opportunities when combined with different materials and <a href=\"handbook://workstations-indappledgroves\">Workstations</a>.

<font weight='bold' align='center'>Basic Concepts</font>
	Tool modes in this mod provide access to different recipes and
therefore different outputs based the tool, crafting station, and
input. Three different tool modes have been implemented as of this
version, with a fourth presently disabled and a fifth being planned.

	Not all tools will have access to the same tool modes, nor will
all tools that have access to a tool mode be guaranteed to be effective
at the indicated process. Some tools are simply better at some things 
than others. For instance, you can hew wood with the backside of a 
<a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:grubaxe-tinbronze\">Grub Axe</a>, but it's not as effective as the same tier <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:adze-wood-tinbronze\">adze</a> will be.

<font weight='bold' align='center'>Tool Modes</font>

<font weight='bold'>Chopping:</font> This mode is used when chopping wood into slabs, firewood, and sticks. May be changed to 'splitting' in a future revision. Found in any form of <a href=\"handbook://item-axe-wood-tinbronze\">axe</a>, including <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:forestaxe-tinbronze\">forest axes</a>, <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:grubaxe-tinbronze\">grub axes</a>, and <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:maul-tinbronze\">mauls</a>.

<font weight='bold'>Hewing:</font> This mode is used when shaping wood or 'peeling' it, such as when removing bark. Currently used only for peeling bark, creating chopping blocks from slabs, and making beams on the <a href=\"handbook://block-indappledgroves:sawbuck-birch-oak-east\">sawbuck</a>. Found in any <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:adze-wood-tinbronze\">adze</a> or <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:grubaxe-tinbronze\">Grub Axe.</a>'

<font weight='bold'>Sawing:</font> This mode is solely used by saws, and is used when making boards out of logs. Found in, unsurprisingly, the <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:saw-copper\">saw.</a>

<font weight='bold' align='center'>Future Modes</font>
<font weight='bold'>Planing:</font>  Planing will be a mode used to process boards from a rough state into a smoothed state when more in-depth board making processes are introduced.

<font weight='bold'>Riving:</font> Riving is a process by which logs can be split into shingles, beams, and various other pieces that require methods more precise than splitting with an axe or maul. A froe, or frow axe is usually used for this process.",

"item-handbooktitle-firewood": "In Dappled Groves Uses:",
"item-handbooktext-firewood": "Can be made by <a href=\"handbook://toolmodes-indappledgroves\">chopping</a> a log slab after placing on the ground, or on a <a href=\"handbook://block-indappledgroves:choppingblock-birch-east\">chopping block</a>. Can be placed on the ground or a <a href=\"handbook://block-indappledgroves:choppingblock-birch-east\">chopping block</a> and processed into sticks by <a href=\"handbook://toolmodes-indappledgroves\">chopping</a> them with an axe or other chopping tool. ",
